summary: SummaryGlow Play Cushiony Blush by MAC is a bouncy, buildable blush that provides glowy color in a lightweight formula with skin-conditioning ingredients.
details: DetailsBenefitsSheer-to-medium, buildable colorLightweight, cushiony textureProvides a healthy-looking, natural glowBlurs the appearance of pores and fine linesSmooth and comfortable applicationSkin-conditioning ingredientsFree of parabens, phthalates, animal-derived ingredientsItem 2626256How To UseSmooth over cheeks or lips with your fingertips, or use a 159S Brush if desired.IngredientsDimethicone, Diisostearyl Malate, Hydrogenated Poly(C6-14 Olefin), Octyldodecanol, Silica, Dimethicone/Vinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Hexyl Laurate, Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Oil, Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil, Tocopherol, Caprylyl Glycol, Tin Oxide, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Propylene Carbonate, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Tocopheryl Acetate, Phenoxyethanol, Sorbic Acid, Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491), Iron Oxides (CI 77492), Iron Oxides (CI 77499), Bismuth Oxychloride (CI 77163), Manganese Violet (CI 77742), Red 6 (CI 15850), Red 7 (CI 15850), Red 30 (CI 73360), Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850), Red 28 Lake (CI 45410), Red 30 Lake (CI 73360), Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140), Yellow 6 Lake (CI 15985)Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.comments: I have been using Mac for 20 years. I bought 2 colors ginger and grand blushes. I have tan Asian skin it gave a natural look its easy to apply on the skin. Will definitely try other colors .

reviews.headline: Favorite Blush Hands Down!
reviews.comments: This blush is amazing! Espejcally if you have a cool undertone. Most blushes make my rosacea look worse but this- this blush is amazing! You need it!

reviews.headline: Perfect Blush
reviews.comments: Love this blush. Not highly pigmented, which is my preference, so easy to apply and layer until just right. I am a cool tone and this slightly peachy tone works perfectly.

reviews.headline: Gorgeous cool tone pink!
reviews.comments: Totally snyced is the prefect cool tone pink shade and it doesn't fade by the end of the day! I have really pale skin and it's hard to find a pink blush that isn't warm. The application is quite buildable, I like to use a dense buffer brush, it helps to pick up the product nicely.

reviews.headline: My go-to blush!
reviews.comments: I was having a hard time finding the perfect blush and the sales girl showed me this blush! Its perfect, soft on skin, buildable coverage! And I love the fact you can use your fingertips for perfect coverage!

reviews.headline: I would buy this product again
reviews.comments: Love the way it blinds in with my skin

reviews.headline: Ok blush, funky smell
reviews.comments: The blush is ok, I like the concept but I cannot get past the smell. I bought one and it smelled rancid so I returned it, then I bought it again and the smell wasn't as strong, but it still doesn't smell great.

reviews.headline: Great Product!!
reviews.comments: I actually REALLY like these! I have been trying to find the products for a beautiful everyday minimal natural makeup look and this is perfect. It can be very sheer but it is very buildable. I love the formula, the packaging, everything about it. You can even pop it in your purse and touch it up throughout the day and it wont disturb the makeup underneath. Definitely recommend these! I would love if they came out with a bronzer in the same formula, that would be a dreamüíï

reviews.headline: Just the right shade
reviews.comments: Thank you to the help I received in picking this product and the right shade.  It adds just the right amount of color to my pale complexion in the winter.

reviews.headline: Peachy pink‚ù§Ô∏è
reviews.comments: Goes on smooth and easy to blend. Love that you can build it up and still has a smooth finish. The color gave me a beautiful glow!

reviews.headline: Just what I needed!
reviews.comments: Color is perfect. Goes on smoothly. Most importantly, does settle in wrinkles like some products.

reviews.headline: Great texture
reviews.comments: Such a light, smooth texture.  Great color.

reviews.headline: Returning this
reviews.comments: Too shiny and too greasy. It came off on my phone immediately.

reviews.headline: The color totally synced is not as advertised at all!
reviews.comments: The formula is a dream! BUT the color I got (totally synced) is darker than the colors online. It's more like a hot pink and not at all a purple or lilac AT ALL. Cool toned yes? Lilac, no! I have very fair cool toned skin and I knew that most makeup products would pull warm on me, so I assumed I was the problem. I tried the blush out on my friend who has a warm tanned complexion, the blush was still light hot pink! Other than that, best formula I have ever used.

reviews.headline: Yes

reviews.headline: the best cream blush ever!!
reviews.comments: This product is absolutely beautiful on the skin. It's very buildable and such a natural tone. It layers great with cream bronzers as well. 10000/10 would buy over and over again!

faceoff_positive.comments:
I recently had the opportunity to try the MAC Glow Play Blush in Grand through a product review opportunity on BzzAgent. I am not only thoroughly impressed by this blush, but also with BzzAgent for providing such a high quality product to test and review. This blush offers a natural, dewy finish that gives my skin a beautiful, healthy glow without looking overly shimmery. The creamy, gel-like texture glides on smoothly and blends effortlessly, making application a breeze.

One of my favorite features of this blush is its buildable coverage. Whether I want a subtle hint of color for a fresh daytime look or a more pronounced flush for an evening out, this blush delivers. It feels lightweight on my skin and stays put throughout the day, which is a huge plus for my busy lifestyle.

However, there are a few considerations to keep in mind. While the gel-cream formula is smooth and easy to apply, it might take some getting used to if you typically use powder blushes. I found that using my fingers or a specific brush designed for cream products worked best. Also, those with very oily skin might prefer a powder blush to combat shine, as this one has a dewy finish.

Overall, the MAC Glow Play Blush in Grand is a fantastic addition to my makeup collection. Its natural finish, buildable coverage, and long-lasting formula make it a standout product. If you're looking for a versatile blush that enhances your skin's radiance, this one is definitely worth trying.
faceoff_positive.headline: My Honest Experience

faceoff_negative.comments: Overall I wanted to love this blush but it seems to have missed the bar a little. I received the blush as a gift from BzzAgent and tried it a few times hoping to like it. The texture is fun and bouncy which is unquote but the colour is very hard to see on my skin tone. I'm pretty pale and I needed to use a lot to see anything. It also isn't as "glowy" as it claims to be. The packaging is nice and it looks nice on the outside but the application with a brush is challenging. I used my fingers and had to layer a lot on to notice any.
faceoff_negative.headline: Interesting Texture with Subtle Pigment
